ast-airbender-live-action-adaptations-222828717.html"><em>降世神通：最后的气宗</em></a></ins>.它还展示了对获得普利策奖的二战小说的改编<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/netflix-shares-teaser-for-world-war-ii-drama-all-the-light-we-cannot-see-211706050.html"><em>所有我们看不见的光</em></a></ins>.</p><p>流光还透露了改编刘慈欣获奖科幻小说的首个预告片<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/netflixs-3-body-problem-first-look-confirms-january-2024-premiere-213927002.html"><em>三体问题</em></a></ins>.这是第一个（完成的）项目，来自《权力的游戏》的共同创作者/共同破坏者大卫贝尼奥夫和 DB Weiss，因为所有<em>这些</em>。</p><p>但可能是最大的新版本是改编自大片反乌托邦的游戏节目<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/netflixs-squid-game-reality-competition-show-debuts-this-november-204334075.html"><em>鱿鱼游戏</em></a></ins>，将于 11 月登陆。该系列赛让 456 名参赛者通过一系列艰苦的挑战，直到一名获胜者获得 456 万美元的奖金。请记住，参与者已经将他们在节目中的经历描述为“绝对不人道”，并且许多参赛者在挑战期间需要医疗护理。讽刺吧？</p><p> – 丹·库珀</p><p><em>The Morning After 不仅仅是一份</em><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/about/newsletter/"><em>时事通讯</em></a><em>——它还是一个每日播客。</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-08-01-engadget-podcasts.html"><em>在这里订阅</em></a><em>，获取周一至周五的每日音频简报</em><em>。</em></p><h3>你可能错过的最重要的故事</h3><h3></h3><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-pixel-8-pro-could-feature-a-flat-display-200049745.html">Pixel 8 Pro 可能配备平面显示器</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-confirms-june-outlook-and-onedrive-outages-were-caused-by-ddos-attacks-173431319.html">微软确认 6 月 Outlook 和 OneDrive 中断是由 DDoS 攻击造成的</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-bravia-tv-owners-can-soon-take-zoom-calls-from-the-couch-213024871.html">索尼 Bravia 电视用户很快可以在沙发上接听 Zoom 电话</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-unexpectedly-sells-its-domain-hosting-business-to-squarespace-183001176.html">谷歌意外将其域名托管业务出售给 Squarespace</a></ins></p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/summer-game-fest-2023-all-the-games-announced-140053892.html">2023 年夏季游戏节：所有游戏公布</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/biden-administration-announces-930-million-in-grants-to-expand-rural-internet-access-153708056.html">拜登政府宣布拨款 9.3 亿美元扩大农村互联网接入</a></ins></p><h2></h2><h2><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-rolls-back-covid-19-misinformation-rules-in-many-countries-174746077.html">Meta 在许多国家/地区取消了 COVID-19 错误信息规则</a></ins></h2><h3>是时候让人们在那拥挤的剧院里大喊“着火了”。</h3><p></p><p> Facebook的母公司有<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-rolls-back-covid-19-misinformation-rules-in-many-countries-174746077.html">收回其对 COVID-19 错误信息的稍微积极的立场</a></ins>.周五晚些时候，它表示将在不再将大流行列为活跃的公共卫生紧急事件的地区放宽规定。在这些国家，比如美国，用户应该预料到谣言、阴谋论和其他无稽之谈会激增。如果你失去了所爱的人，无论是由于流行病本身还是它的二阶效应之一，都可以认为这是马克扎克伯格直接对你的对他们记忆的一种尖锐侮辱。</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-rolls-back-covid-19-misinformation-rules-in-many-countries-174746077.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></ins></p><h2><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-designers-on-why-the-pixel-fold-isnt-just-another-foldable-153058971.html">谷歌的设计师为什么 Pixel Fold 不仅仅是另一个可折叠的</a></ins></h2><h3>了解有关制作折叠式手机的所有尝试。</h3><figure> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-designers-on-why-the-pixel-fold-isnt-just-another-foldable-153058971.html"><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/24ebd670-0e8c-11ee-bdea-b68d23bb4589" style="height:351px;width:625px;" alt="来自 Google Pixel Fold 的一些设计元素的图像被放置在桌子上。" data-uuid="12a58b2a-298a-37a4-9005-420f6e766cd6"></a><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-designers-on-why-the-pixel-fold-isnt-just-another-foldable-153058971.html">谷歌</a></div></figure><p>三星在可折叠设备领域的主导地位给谷歌等新进入者带来了压力，他们无法被视为在追赶。<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-designers-on-why-the-pixel-fold-isnt-just-another-foldable-153058971.html">在 Pixel Fold 发布之前</a></ins>, Sam Rutherford 与设备背后的两个人 George Hwang 和 Andrea Zvinakis 坐了下来。三人讨论了前置显示器的重要性、为多屏设备开发软件的挑战以及为什么我们仍然需要智能地使用铰链。继续阅读以了解构建将受到如此严格审查的内容的所有想法。</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/googles-designers-on-why-the-pixel-fold-isnt-just-another-foldable-153058971.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></ins></p><h2><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-reddit-blackout-is-already-forcing-unexpected-changes-103521266.html">Reddit 停电已经迫使意想不到的变化</a></ins></h2><h3><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/reddits-average-daily-traffic-fell-during-blackout-according-to-third-party-data-194721801.html">第三方分析数据显示，抗议活动确实导致交通量下降。</a></ins></h3><p></p><p> Karissa Bell 写了一份详尽的报告<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-reddit-blackout-is-already-forcing-unexpected-changes-103521266.html">现在 Reddit 上发生的一切</a></ins>，值得您关注。随着首席执行官史蒂夫霍夫曼继续进攻，威胁要罢免抗议的版主，这场斗争已经损害了该平台的声誉。一些社区正在寻找替代场所，而一些广告商则按下暂停键以避开骚乱。而且，正如霍夫曼在事情上装出一副勇敢的面孔一样，分析人士认为，抗议活动确实引起了<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/reddits-average-daily-traffic-fell-during-blackout-according-to-third-party-data-194721801.html">明显下降</a></ins>在 Reddit 的每日流量中。</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-reddit-blackout-is-already-forcing-unexpected-changes-103521266.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></ins></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/binance-reaches-deal-with-sec-to-avoid-us-asset-freeze-164802356.html">币安与美国证券交易委员会达成协议以避免美国资产冻结</a></ins></h2><h3>暂缓执行，至少现在是这样。</h3><p></p><p>在解决其诉讼之前，SEC 将允许<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/binance-reaches-deal-with-sec-to-avoid-us-asset-freeze-164802356.html">币安将继续在美国运营</a></ins>.官员以各种涉嫌不当行为为由起诉该交易所，并最初试图完全冻结其资产，从根本上使其停业。但一名法官迫使币安做出妥协，允许币安继续运营，只做足够的事情来保护其用户的资产，并在法庭闹剧正式开始之前允许提款。</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/binance-reaches-deal-with-sec-to-avoid-us-asset-freeze-164802356.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></ins></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-all-the-cool-things-netflix-showed-off-over-the-weekend-111523740.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-all-the-cool-things-netflix-showed-off-over-the-weekend-111523740.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9af432bd-9fcf-4a06-920b-069b0639bea6</guid><dc:creator>丹尼尔·库珀</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 19 Jun 2023 11:15:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687171174</ingested><modified> 2023-06-19T10:39:40+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="2294" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/4d47f060-0e8a-11ee-9dff-cd2fc483c235" width="3500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2294" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/4d47f060-0e8a-11ee-9dff-cd2fc483c235" width="3500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Alexandre Schneider via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[SAO PAULO, BRAZIL - JUNE 17: General view of the Netflix's Tudum: A Global Fan Event 2023 at Fundação Bienal de São Paulo on June 17, 2023 in Sao Paulo, Brazil. (Photo by Alexandre Schneider/Getty Images for NETFLIX)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Tudum: A Global Fan Event]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The FCC is preparing to take a 'fresh look' at internet data caps]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>根据<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2023/06/fcc-chair-to-investigate-exactly-how-much-everyone-hates-data-caps/"><em>Ars Technica</em></a>发现的一份<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://docs.fcc.gov/public/attachments/DOC-394416A1.pdf">FCC 文件，</a>联邦通信委员会 (FCC) 主席杰西卡·罗森沃塞尔 (Jessica Rosenworcel) 希望就互联网数据上限对消费者的影响发布正式的调查通知。信中称，监管机构还将考虑“采取行动”以确保数据上限不会损害竞争或影响宽带服务的访问。</p><p> Rosenworcel 在一份声明中说：“互联网接入不再是可有可无的东西，而是每个人、任何地方都需要拥有的东西。” “当我们需要访问互联网时，我们不会考虑完成一项任务需要多少数据，我们只知道它需要完成。现在是 FCC 重新审视数据上限如何影响消费者和竞争的时候了”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>信中称，通过调查通知，FCC 将“征求意见，以更好地理解为什么尽管消费者的宽带需求增加，而且提供商已证明有提供无限数据计划的技术能力，但数据上限的使用仍在继续存在”。</p><p>不过，Rosenworcel 目前无法对数据上限采取任何行动。 FCC 目前只有四名成员（两名民主党人和两名共和党人），因为参议院拒绝确认拜登总统的第一位提名人 Gigi Sohn，她随后<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/public-internet-advocate-gigi-sohn-withdraws-from-fcc-consideration-201020427.html">撤回了自己的名字</a>以供考虑。白宫此后提名了电信律师安娜戈麦斯，她<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/05/22/biden-nominates-telecom-attorney-anna-gomez-to-fcc.html">似乎得到了电信行业的支持</a>。戈麦斯的提名听证会定于本周四，6 月 22 日举行。</p><p>在 COVID-19 大流行期间，宽带提供商 Comcast 暂时取消了数据上限，但它继续对美国某些地区的某些合同施加<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Xfinity;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ae1f1c5e-7717-478b-ad5c-c0b7029ab199&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Xfinity&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZ1CWkeZAFO7KDtOfYudBx4tFOxszL9BXUbRJL1QKv6P&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.xfinity.com%2Fsupport%2Farticles%2Fdata-usage-what-is-the-terabyte-data-usage-plan" class="rapid-with-clickid">1.2TB 的数据上限</a>。 Charter 与 FCC 达成的不对其 Spectrum 服务施加数据上限的协议（在收购时代华纳时受到打击）于今年结束，但该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.lightreading.com/broadband/charter-has-no-plans-to-add-data-caps-when-fcc-ban-lifts/d/d-id/784184?">最近表示</a>“没有计划在条件到期时 [重新启动数据上限]。”</p><p>除了拟议的调查通知，FCC 还开设了一个新门户网站，允许消费者在<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://consumercomplaints.fcc.gov/hc/en-us/articles/16136257875348-Data-Caps-Experience-Form">fcc.gov/datacapstories</a>上分享数据上限如何影响他们（在固定或无线宽带网络上）。该委员会写道，这将有助于 FCC 确定数据上限如何影响“包括残疾人、低收入消费者和历史上处于不利地位的社区，以及在线教育、远程医疗和远程工作”的每个人的访问。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/the-fcc-is-preparing-to-take-a-fresh-look-at-internet-data-caps-084245899.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-fcc-is-preparing-to-take-a-fresh-look-at-internet-data-caps-084245899.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 26d8148b-6a48-494a-bc32-b4114c2798b1</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 19 Jun 2023 08:42:45 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687164167</ingested><modified> 2023-06-19T08:42:53+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Professional Services]]></category><category><![CDATA[Loans]]></category><category><![CDATA[Internet & Networking Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="4940" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/124e66e0-0e73-11ee-b6ff-0e98a636e83b" width="7408"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifi